[When reading the above report, this moderator had a flashback of an
observation made years ago upon return from a one month stay in a
geographic area known for high levels of "travellers diarrhea" having not
had any untoward illness during or following the trip. When asked by
colleagues on the gastroenterology service what was used as prevention, I
said "EtOH (ethanol) beginning around 12 noon daily". Seems to confirm the
adage that many a true word is said in jest. - Mod.MPP]
